---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Draft about page for Can Ocek's multidisciplinary work across technology, business, and music."
>
  <header class="page-header container narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Across systems, strategy, and sound</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Can studies Management & Technology at the Technical University of Munich and keeps building
      from a computer-science foundation into software, data, business systems, music, and media.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="about-trajectory-title">
    <div class="container two-column">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Trajectory</p>
        <h2 id="about-trajectory-title">Technical and creative foundations</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="stack">
        <p>
          The site should eventually explain the move from Informatics into Management &
          Technology without treating technical and business work as separate identities.
        </p>
        <p>
          The same profile also needs room for music: guitar, vocals, arrangement, production,
          live audio, and visual media are part of the main story.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="about-work-title">
    <div class="container two-column">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Working style</p>
        <h2 id="about-work-title">The useful pattern</h2>
      </div>
      <ul class="meta-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Understand the system</strong>
          <p>Map the technical, business, and creative constraints before choosing a solution.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Find the missing pieces</strong>
          <p>Identify what blocks the project: data, workflow, presentation, tooling, or execution.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Connect disciplines</strong>
          <p>Move between implementation, communication, and production instead of isolating them.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
